## Bug ID: 
[speed conrol 001]

## Summary:
[Text speed does not change accurately going from max to min speed (4.5x to .5x)]

## Environment:
- **Browser/Device: Chrome** 
- **OS: Windows 11** 
- **Speechify Version: Web app** 
- **User Type: Free** 

## Severity:
Medium/Low

## Priority:
P2

## Steps to Reproduce:
1. Opened a PDF document in Speechify Web App
2. Started playing the audio (default speed 1.0x)
3. Clicked the speed control button
4. Change speed to 4.5x
5. Audio changes correctly to max speed
6. click speed control
7. Change speed to .5x

## Expected Result:
Visual slider will change to .5x and audio should change correctly to min speed .5x

## Actual Result:
visual slider will change to .5x but audio will remain at max speed (4.5x)

## Screenshots/Evidence:
N/A

## Reproducibility:
Reproduced 4/5 times

## Additional Notes:
Refreshing the page will then fix the speed issue to match the visual slider at .5x
- This only occurs when going from max to min settings, not from min to max speed settings or anything in between.
